To find the amount of capital contributed by shareholders in exchange for shares, we look at the "Paid-in Capital" line item on the balance sheet, both at the initial and end dates. This item represents the capital contributed by shareholders when the shares were issued and any changes over the period.

From the provided data:
- Initial Paid-in Capital (2023-12-31): 13,000,000.00
- End Paid-in Capital (2024-02-05): 13,000,000.00

The amount remains the same, indicating no additional capital was contributed during this period.

Therefore, the initial and final values of shareholder contributions are both 13,000,000.00.
